comment.author: 47524421@N08
comment._content: Consolidated B-24M-45-CO Liberator 44-42722. Designated Line Number 6658, this B-24M was the 6,725th and last Liberator built by Consolidated Vultee at San Diego, and was destined to become an F-7 photo ship, converted at Tucson, AZ. The Liberator contract was officially terminated in June of 1945 and the last B-24M rolled off the line at Convair/San Diego in that month, although some sources say this bomber was started on May 18 and finished on May 25. I found these photos, which unfortunately look like they were scanned with a pointy rock, but you get the idea.
